Class Little_car_panel.TimerObstacles

  • java.lang.Object
    • little_car.Little_car_panel.TimerObstacles
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.awt.event.ActionListener, java.util.EventListener
    Enclosing class:
    Little_car_panel

    private class Little_car_panel.TimerObstacles
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.awt.event.ActionListener
    The ActionListener for the timer is created in a private class The ActionListener defines what happens every delay-milliseconds defined in the timer: - a new number between 0 and 420 (JPanel's width) is randomly generated - a new Obstacle with x-position defined by the randomly-generated number is created and added to list1 - the move_down() method is invoked on all Obstacles inside list1 - the check_collision() method is invoked
